Key Match Events: The Bulls overcame a 19-point deficit in the third quarter and took their first lead of the night on Coby White’s driving layup with 47.1 seconds left in the fourth quarter, making it 111-110.
San Antonio went scoreless over the game’s final 3:52.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Bulls didn’t register their first points until a White layup at the 8:18 mark of the first quarter.
San Antonio shot 46.3 percent from the field compared to 43.1 percent for Chicago.
Others: Victor Wembanyama had 23 points and 14 rebounds to go along with eight blocks while pacing eight Spurs scorers in double figures.
Julian Champagnie scored 12 points, Jeremy Sochan, Devin Vassell, and Keldon Johnson each had 11, and Harrison Barnes and Stephon Castle chipped in 10 apiece.
